# ~/.claude/.gitignore — allowlist model.
#
# Claude Code writes several GB of machine state, caches, session transcripts,
# history, and secrets into this directory. We version-control ONLY durable,
# portable, shareable config. Everything else is ignored by default so it can
# never be accidentally `dotfiles add`-ed (defense-in-depth on top of the bare
# repo's status.showUntrackedFiles=no).
#
# To onboard a new portable file/dir: add a `!`-rule below, then
#   dotfiles add ~/.claude/<path>

# 1. Ignore everything.
*

# 2. Re-include the portable config, by explicit path.
!.gitignore
!CLAUDE.md
!settings.json
!keybindings.json
!hooks/
!hooks/**
!skills/
!skills/**
!commands/
!commands/**
!agents/
!agents/**
!output-styles/
!output-styles/**

# NOTE: settings.json is tracked, but only after its inert `mcpServers` block
# (which held an unused inline OAuth client secret) was removed. Claude Code
# reads MCP server definitions from ~/.claude.json / .mcp.json, NOT from
# settings.json, so keep server configs — and any secrets they carry — out of
# this file and out of the repo.
# settings.local.json is machine-local and must stay ignored.
